[{"id":"c430fdfdd9db6aff405a5833ee564543","from":"Faculty of 1000","from_email":"info@updates.f1000.com","to":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to_list":[{"name":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Your journal club organized with F1000Prime","date":"2014-01-22T17:01:30.000Z","formatted_date":"Jan 22, 2014","formatted_time":"5:01 PM","body":"F1000Prime | http://f1000.com/prime \n=====================================\n\nJANUARY 2014\n\nWe've added a new service to F1000Prime [ http://f1000.com/prime ] that integrates journal clubs with F1000Prime's unique database of the best research identified by nearly 6,000 senior scientists [ http://f1000.com/prime/thefaculty ], including nine Nobel Prize winners.\n\nF1000Journal Clubs [ http://f1000.com/prime/journalclubs/ ] is an online tool to help scientists create, organize, and share the conclusions of, their journal clubs.\n\n\nFeatures of F1000Journal Clubs: \n~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ \n   \n* Online meeting scheduler   \n  \n* Integration with F1000Prime and PubMed to personally recommend relevant articles to you  \n  \n* Article short-listing and journal club member voting  \n  \n* PDF figure extractor to assist in creating presentations  \n  \n* Audiovisual resource uploading tools  \n  \n* Journal club report writing, commenting and sharing tools  \n\n\nF1000Journal Clubs is available to all subscribers to F1000Prime. Please recommend F1000Prime to your organization's library [ http://f1000.com/prime/recommend/academic ] to benefit from all these features.\n\nAlternatively, you can take out a personal subscription [ http://f1000.com/prime/register/personalsub ] including a free one-month trial. If a subscriber to F1000Prime invites someone to join an F1000Journal Club who is not part of a subscribing institute, or who does not have a personal subscription, the invitee will receive three months free access to the club and all features of F1000Prime when they register [ http://f1000.com/prime/journalclubs/register ].\n\nIf you have questions or feedback about F1000Prime please join one of our online demonstrations [ http://www.f1000prime.eventbrite.co.uk/ ] or reply to this email.\n\nBest regards,\n\nIain Hrynaszkiewicz\nOutreach Director, F1000Prime\n\n\n=====================================\n\nYou have received this message because you asked to receive the F1000 Monthly Update and related news to your registered email address jeeproject@yahoo.com from Faculty of 1000. To stop receiving this type of information from Faculty of 1000, reply to this email with the word \"remove\" in the subject line. For further information or enquiries please contact info@f1000.com [ mailto:info@f1000.com ].\n\nF1000, Faculty of 1000 Ltd | Science Navigation Group   \nRegistered in England and Wales with Company Number 3739756.     \nMiddlesex House | 34-42 Cleveland Street | London W1T 4LB | United Kingdom\n","body_html":"<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" />\n<title>Your journal club organized with F1000Prime</title>\n<!--general stylesheet-->\n<style type=\"text/css\">\n.body {\tfont-family: Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n\tfont-size: 12px;\n\tline-height: normal;\n\tfont-weight: normal;\n\ttext-transform: none;\n\tcolor: #383838;\n}\n\t.foot {font-family: Arial,  Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:10px; background-color:#FFFFFF}\n\ta {color: #CB2D2C; text-decoration: underline ; font-weight: bold}\n\timg {border:0; border-style:none}\t\n\th4 {color:#000000; font-size:larger}\n\nimg { border: none; }\np { padding: 0; margin: 0; }\nh1, h2, h3, p, li, a, td { font-family: arial,sans-serif; }\ntd { vertical-align:top;}\nul { margin: 10;}\n.heading {\nborder-radius: 3px;\n-webkit-border-radius: 3px;\n-moz-border-radius: 3px;\n-khtml-border-radius: 3px;\n-ica